None of this makes any sense to me. From what I know of the 
development of the Arabic number system, ever since the place-value 
system was discovered (borrowed from India) the number ten has always 
been represented by two digits, namely "10"; that is what the place 
value system means. See this page for that history:

  http://www-history.mcs.st-and.ac.uk/HistTopics/Arabic_numerals.html

Perhaps you can tell me what "old Arabic" system you are referring 
to -- what is the date of its use, and what symbols did it use, and 
did it use place value?

